5000|$|<b>Straight</b> <b>whiskey</b> is whiskey {{that was}} {{distilled}} to {{not more than}} 80 percent alcohol by volume (160 proof) that has been aged {{for at least two}} years at a starting alcohol concentration of not more than 62.5% and has not been blended with any other spirits, colorings, or additives. A <b>straight</b> <b>whiskey</b> that also meets one of the other above definitions is referred to by combining the term [...] "straight" [...] with the term for the type of whiskey. For example, a rye whiskey that meets this definition is called a [...] "straight rye whiskey".|$|E
